I"\<h1 id="introduction">Introduction</h1>

<p>In this tutorial I’ll show you how to make a drawable and draggable paper in Godot. The result will look like this:</p>

<p><img src="/assets/images/posts/tutorial_1/result.gif" alt="Result" /></p>

<p>This tutorial is more aimed for people with a bit of knowledge in Godot.</p>

<h1 id="project-settings">Project settings</h1>

<p>The only changes I did to the project settings were made under <em>Display/Window</em></p>

<div class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge"><div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight"><code>Width = 320
Height = 180
...
Test Width = 1280
Test Height = 720
...
Mode = 2d
Aspect = expand
</code></pre></div></div>

<h1 id="creating-the-main-scene">Creating the main scene</h1>

<p>First we create the main scene. As we want to make a 2D game, we choose as our root node a 2D scene and call it “Main”. Next we want to create the paper.</p>

